The paper deals with a fundamental geometric tool, convex hulls, and presents experimental results related to the number of convex vertices in natural datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these results for pre-allocated arrays and output-sensitive algorithms, which are topics related to Data Structures (cs.DS) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories, respectively. The paper also mentions the use of random models of data, which is a topic related to Data Mining (cs.DM) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
